01b[0m\u001b[37m━\u001b[0m \u001b[1m0s\u001b[0m 3ms/step - accuracy: 0.5697 - loss: 1.9869\nEpoch 29: val_loss improved from 1.81283 to 1.81059, saving model to /kaggle/working/models/ast_mlp.keras\n\u001b[1m196/196\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1s\u001b[0m 4ms/step - accuracy: 0.5696 - loss: 1.9875 - val_accuracy: 0.6428 - val_loss: 1.8106 - learning_rate: 0.0010\nEpoch 30/30\n\u001b[1m184/196\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m━━\u001b[0m \u001b[1m0s\u001b[0m 3ms/step - accuracy: 0.5714 - loss: 1.9791\nEpoch 30: val_loss improved from 1.81059 to 1.77154, saving model to /kaggle/working/models/ast_mlp.keras\n\u001b[1m196/196\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1s\u001b[0m 4ms/step - accuracy: 0.5712 - loss: 1.9806 - val_accuracy: 0.6519 - val_loss: 1.7715 - learning_rate: 0.0010\nRestoring model weights from the end of the best epoch: 30.\n\n=======================================================\n  AST features + MLP\n=======================================================\n  Accuracy:    0.6519  (65.19%)\n  F1 Macro:    0.6509\n  F1 Weighted: 0.6509\n  Precision:   0.6889\n  Recall:      0.6519\n  Tiempo:      32.20s\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1000x800 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Autores con acc = 1.0:  81\n  Autores con acc = 0.0:  7\n  Accuracy media por clase: 0.6519\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 900x400 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":14},{"id":"051ca1e7-947f-4301-a541-fbe70d91121d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Modelo 4 — AST C++ + TF-IDF n-gramas + MLP (modelo combinado)\n\nEste modelo fusiona dos representaciones complementarias del código fuente. El vector TF-IDF de n-gramas de caracteres captura patrones superficiales de estilo: indentación, puntuación, operadores. El vector AST captura la estructura lógica del programa: cuántas funciones define el autor, si prefiere bucles `for` o `while`, cómo anida sus condicionales.\n\nLa hipótesis es que ambas representaciones son ortogonales — aportan información distinta — y que su concatenación permite al modelo aprender un fingerprint más completo del estilo del programador que cualquiera de las dos por separado. La fusión se hace concatenando los dos vectores antes de pasarlos a la red, lo que es equivalente a un early fusion de features.","metadata":{}},{"id":"caf19854-81d1-4ebf-86cc-187d7113711d","cell_type":"code","source":"# El TF-IDF char ya está ajustado (tfidf_c). Para el modelo combinado\n# se usa max_features=10000 en lugar de 20000 para que la concatenación\n# con el AST quepa en RAM. El vectorizador se guarda por separado.\n\ntfidf_c_combined = load_vectorizer_if_exists('tfidf_char_combined')\n\nif tfidf_c_combined is None:\n    tfidf_c_combined = TfidfVectorizer(\n        analyzer='char',\n        ngram_range=(2, 4),\n        max_features=10000,\n        sublinear_tf=True\n    )\n    tfidf_c_combined.fit(train_df['source_code'].astype(str))\n    save_vectorizer('tfidf_char_combined', tfidf_c_combined)\n\n# Reuse ast_vocab from the individual AST model\nast_vocab_m4 = ast_vocab\n\n# Sparse-to-dense en batches para no saturar RAM\nBATCH = 5000\n\ndef build_combined(texts):\n    \"\"\"\n    Construye la matriz combinada TF-IDF char + AST en batches.\n    TF-IDF es sparse; AST es denso pero pequeño.\n    Se convierten en bloques de BATCH filas para evitar OOM.\n    \"\"\"\n    tfidf_sparse = tfidf_c_combined.transform(texts.astype(str))\n    ast_matrix, _ = ast_vectorize(texts.tolist(), vocab=ast_vocab_m4)\n\n    parts = []\n    for start in range(0, tfidf_sparse.shape[0], BATCH):\n        end  = start + BATCH\n        tfidf_chunk = tfidf_sparse[start:end].toarray().astype('float32')\n        ast_chunk   = ast_matrix[start:end]\n        parts.append(np.concatenate([tfidf_chunk, ast_chunk], axis=1))\n    return np.vstack(parts)\n\n\nprint('Construyendo matriz combinada train...')\nX_train_combined = build_combined(train_df['source_code'])\nprint('Construyendo matriz combinada dev...')\nX_dev_combined   = build_combined(dev_df['source_code'])\nprint(f'TF-IDF char features: {tfidf_c_combined.max_features}')\nprint(f'AST features:         {len(ast_vocab_m4)}')\nprint(f'Combined input shape:  {X_train_combined.shape}')\n\nmodel_combined = load_keras_if_exists('combined_mlp')\n\nif model_combined is None:\n    model_combined = Sequential([\n        Dense(512, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train_combined.shape[1],)),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.5),\n        Dense(256, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.4),\n        Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n        BatchNormalization(),\n        Dropout(0.3),\n        Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')\n    ], name='combined_mlp')\n    model_combined.compile(\n        optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=5e-4),\n        loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n        metrics=['accuracy']\n    )\n    model_combined.summary()\n    t0 = time.time()\n    model_combined.fit(\n        X_train_combined, y_train,\n        validation_data=(X_dev_combined, y_dev),\n        epochs=30,\n        batch_size=256,\n        callbacks=get_callbacks('combined_mlp'),\n        verbose=1\n    )\n    t1 = time.time()\nelse:\n    t0 = t1 = time.time()\n\ny_pred_combined = le.inverse_transform(\n    np.argmax(model_combined.predict(X_dev_combined, verbose=0), axis=1)\n)\n\nevaluate('AST + TF-IDF char + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_combined,\n         t1 - t0 if t1 > t0 else None)\nplot_full_cm('AST + TF-IDF char + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_combined)\nplot_per_class_acc_hist('AST + TF-IDF char + MLP', y_dev_labels, y_pred_combined)\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-29T21:21:25.499472Z","iopub.execute_input"